body:
@jaylindquist I am thinking db migration is a necessary, as well as updating dashboard save `default_filters` metadata. Otherwise user will `always` see 2 patterns in preselect_filters parameter, and will feel confused. 
Even after db migration that converted all old formation into new format, in the frontend code I still prefer to handle both patterns (at least for a while), because some users use API to generate dashboard requests, or may copy urls somewhere.

Thanks for bringing the feature and code cleanup.

as we refactor all charts to use a consistent API and move them to `@superset-ui` as chart plugins (which users can then pick/choose from at their will), it'd be helpful for us to not add additional charts which will then need migration.

@jeffreythewang if we help with documentation for how to create such a plugin / do this migration now, would you be open to making this a chart plugin that lives outside the superset repository? 

cc @kristw @xtinec @conglei
